  "method": "We propose Decoupled-Critic Data Aggregation (DeC-DAgger), a bootstrapped training loop that separates generation, evaluation, and supervision to prevent error reinforcement. Maintain three roles: (1) a generator G_t that produces outputs on inputs sampled from the current deployment distribution; (2) an external critic C_t that scores outputs using task-grounded signals calibrated on a small, periodically refreshed gold set; and (3) a pseudo-demonstrator D_t that can construct improved targets for hard cases using extra information or alternative solution procedures. Crucially, C_t and D_t are architecturally and objective-wise decoupled from G_t to avoid self-approval and style drift.\n\nAt each iteration, draw a batch of inputs. For coverage, stratify sampling across slices of the input space (by topic/domain clusters in an embedding space) and maintain per-slice quotas to prevent collapse onto easy or frequent modes. For each input x, sample up to k diverse candidates from G_t (stochastic decoding with diversity penalties), but cap k to a small number and evaluate with pairwise duels to mitigate pool-size bias. Score candidates with C_t and compute G_t’s epistemic signal using a lightweight uncertainty head (single-pass latent discriminant uncertainty). Retain a candidate only if it passes (a) critic-thresholded quality, (b) low generator uncertainty, and (c) augmentation-stability: minor input perturbations or paraphrases yield semantically equivalent outputs per a content-focused checker. Weight retained pairs (x, y^) by w = softclip(C_t(y^)) × (1 − u_G(y^)), normalize within each slice, and admit them to a replay buffer D_p with diversity control (reject near-duplicates in embedding space) to keep support wide.\n\nFor inputs that fail the filter yet are high-value (uncertain, underrepresented slices, or business-critical), route to a pseudo-demonstrator D_t. D_t is allowed stronger tools than G_t: retrieval-augmented re-solving, constraint checking, or a more informed policy that optimizes task-specific objectives unavailable to G_t (e.g., global search, simulators, or verifiers). When D_t provides a target, add it with a higher trust weight w_e. Mix supervision from three sources during student training: gold data D_h, high-trust pseudo targets from D_t, and filtered self-generated data D_p. Optimize a weighted loss L = λ_h L(D_h) + λ_e E_{(x,y_e)}[w_e ℓ(x,y_e)] + λ_p E_{(x,y^)}[w ℓ(x,y^)], with per-slice temperature scaling to keep the effective sample sizes stable across slices.\n\nUpdate the deployed generator by distilling a student S_t on the mixed data while keeping a slow-moving teacher T_t = EMA(T_{t−1}, S_t). Use uncertainty-guided momentum: increase the EMA update rate on parameters primarily responsible for confidently correct samples and damp updates where the teacher shows persistent uncertainty, preventing over-commitment to brittle patterns. Between rounds, recalibrate C_t on a small active set drawn from the decision boundary (high critic variance or generator–critic disagreements), and add a handful of human labels to anchor the critic. Monitor anti-collapse metrics on a held-out gold validation set: slice-level accuracy, calibration, and support coverage (e.g., MMD between current and baseline feature distributions). If drift is detected, tighten critic thresholds, lower k, increase λ_h/λ_e, and widen sampling quotas for degraded slices.\n\nFinally, guard against style over-optimization by structuring C_t around substance-first checks. Prefer reference-based or constraint-satisfaction signals over purely stylistic features, incorporate pairwise preference testing over absolute self-scores, and require evidence attestation where applicable (e.g., retrieval citations or executable checks). This decoupled, stratified, and uncertainty-aware aggregation expands the data frontier without collapsing onto the model’s current biases.",
  "rationale": "Self-training fails when the model both proposes and judges its own outputs; this amplifies stylistic preferences and perceived fluency rather than true task gains. DeC-DAgger breaks this loop by decoupling the critic from the generator, limiting candidate pool bias, and relying on substance-first evaluation, directly addressing known self-bias failure modes. Uncertainty and stability filters further ensure that only reliable, semantically consistent self-labels are admitted, while stratified sampling and diversity control maintain coverage and prevent the dataset from collapsing to easy regions.\n\nWhere the model is weak, a pseudo-demonstrator supplies stronger supervision using additional information or algorithms, akin to an interactive expert in data-aggregation methods. Mixing gold, demonstrator, and filtered self-generated data with calibrated weights, plus a slow uncertainty-guided teacher update, yields steady improvement while constraining drift. Periodic critic recalibration and active sampling around the boundary keep the quality signal honest, providing a robust bootstrap that grows training data without reinforcing existing errors or narrowing the distribution.",
